_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-apo","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":35138,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/01\/allah-expiates-sickness\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Allah expiates sins with disease","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Jubayr ibn Mut\u2019im reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah Almighty will put His servant to trial by illness until his every sin is expiated.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 1548 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064f\u0637\u0652\u0639\u0650\u0645\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3150,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/05\/08\/fever-expiates-fire-gold\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Sickness: Fever expiates sins, just as fire purifies gold","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Umm al-Ala reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, visited me when I was sick, and he said, \u201cBe cheerful, O mother of al-Ala. When a Muslim is sick, Allah takes away his sins just as fire takes away impurities in gold and silver.\u201d Source: Sunan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34456,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/05\/every-salat-expiates-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Every prayer expiates your sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Ayyub reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, every prayer makes the sins before you fall away.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 23503 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f\u0648\u0628\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36258,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/21\/hasanat-expiates-past-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Tawbah: Good deeds expiate past sins in life","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever does good in what remains of his life, he will be forgiven for what has passed. Whoever does evil in what remains of his life, he will be taken to account for what has passed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32995,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/waiting-salat-in-jamaah\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Masajid: Waiting in between congregational prayers expiates sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cShall I not tell you of that by which Allah expiates sins? Thorough ablution despite hardship, working your feet in walking to the mosque, and waiting in between prayers will fully cleanse one of sins.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 505\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26755,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/08\/15\/sujud-sajdah-in-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":40014,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Sujud: Allah expiates sins by prostration in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 15, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubadah ibn al-Samit reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo servant prostrates for the sake of Allah but that Allah will record for him one good deed, erase one bad deed, and raise his status by a degree. Thus, perform many prostrations.\u201d Source: Sunan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_conte